      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Thank you for the explanation. I'm not sure I totally agree and would prefer that if the HOST is an unspecified HOST, we set `total_required_KiB` to `avail_KiB` (line 145). \r\n\r\nI think it would be far worse to fail during a long-running process due to underestimating the space required vs finishing the build but with more space than was needed.\r\n\r\nSaid differently, if we haven't specified anything for a host, assume the worst and use all the space available.",
      "commit_id" : "aa9a48bb8af7a7f1bef98051a1590de3713c7789",
      "created_at" : "2021-12-29T16:02:17Z",
